This is Section 1 of the Digital Personal Data Protection Act, 2023.
This section has two main parts:
​Name of the Law (Short Title): This law will officially be called the 'Digital Personal Data Protection Act, 2023'.
​When will the law come into effect? (Commencement): This law will be considered active from the day the Central Government announces it in the Official Gazette (an official government notification). If the government wishes, it can bring different parts (provisions) of this law into effect on different dates.

Suppose a school creates a new 'Rulebook'.
​The Name: The school names this rulebook "School Rules 2026". (This is the first part of the section).
​Coming into effect: The school Principal puts up a notice on the bulletin board (like a government notification) stating when these rules will start applying.
​Different dates: The Principal decides that:
​The Uniform (Dress Code) rule will apply from August 1st.
​The Mobile Phone Ban rule will apply from August 15th.
​The Late Fine rule will apply from September 1st.
​This means the entire rulebook is not implemented all at once. When we talk about the 'Uniform rule', its commencement will be considered as August 1st, not September 1st.

Similarly, instead of enforcing this massive data protection law all at once across the country, the Government of India can implement its various sections gradually. This gives companies and the general public enough time to adapt to it.
